descript.abstract: Major and Minor Subdivision Activity layer for Anne Arundel County, MD. Current working featureclass
descript.purpose:
This map layer is used to delineate Active Subdivisions. The active subdivisions include the following categories to be displayed on the map. There is a .Lyr file to automate this classification (N:/mapdata/avls/Major Minor Subdivision Activity.lyr). Here are the categories shown as Active on the maps:
sfa - Major Subdivision, Final Phase spa - Major Subdivision, Preformal Phase ska - Major Subdivision, Sketch Phase msa - Active Minor Subdivision pp - Preliminary Plan
The intended application of this data is to serve as a spatial reference of data layers in GIS and mapping applications. It is specifically not intended to be used as a land survey or representation of land for conveyance or tax purposes. It is expected that data created in this project will be replaced as updated information is collected.

stdorder.fees: Fees are listed under Ordering Instructions below.
stdorder.ordering:
Standard ordering for Planning & Zoning's public maps can be made visiting our Publications/Maps/Information Services Counter on the 4th floor of 2664 Riva Road, Annapolis, MD 21401. For any questions pertaining to public map sales, contact this Map Counter at either (410) 222-7463 or (410) 222-7464. For any questions regarding the data that is displayed on the maps, contact Charlie Abrahamson in Planning & Zoning GIS at (410) 222-7744.
Fees: Public maps may be purchased at the Planning & Zoning GIS map desk at 2664 Riva Road, Annapolis, MD on the 4th floor ("Publications/Maps/Information Services Desk.") Their phone number is (410) 222-7463 or 7464. All public paper map prices are as follows: 8 ½ x 11 maps = $5.00; 11 x 17 maps = $6.00; 30 x 40 maps = $40.00; Topographic map 8 ½ x 11 section = $5.00; Entire topographic map sheet = $50.00, Half topographic map = $25.00.
stdorder.turnarnd: Turnaround times on data requests are contingent upon the extent of the request. A simple reprint of a map or copy of existing data can be completed usually in one to two weeks, depending on the current project load. A more complex request, including new data creation or data updates, can take a few weeks depending again on the amount of work necessary.
stdorder.nondig: Hardcopy maps include 30x40 inches, 11x17 inches, and 8.5x11 inches in size.

distinfo.techpreq: Technical prerequisites for using this data digitally include possessing the general knowledge about GIS and mapping, and having access to use some type of GIS viewer. GIS viewing software may include ArcExplorer (free downloadable map viewer from www.esri.com ), ArcView, or ArcInfo, for example.

dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This map layer is used to delineate Active Subdivisions. The active subdivisions include the following categories to be displayed on the map. There is a .Lyr file to automate this classification (N:/mapdata/avls/Major Minor Subdivision Activity.lyr). Here are the categories shown as Active on the maps:
sfa - Major Subdivision, Final Phase spa - Major Subdivision, Preformal Phase ska - Major Subdivision, Sketch Phase msa - Active Minor Subdivision pp - Preliminary Plan
The intended application of this data is to serve as a spatial reference of data layers in GIS and mapping applications. It is specifically not intended to be used as a land survey or representation of land for conveyance or tax purposes. It is expected that data created in this project will be replaced as updated information is collected.
